  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is typically addressed under criminal legislation. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, usually by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations that make it a serious criminal offense, with potential penalties including:\n\n1. Significant financial fines\n2. Imprisonment\n3. Asset seizure\n4. Criminal prosecution\n\nThe specific legal framework and penalties vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is generally treated as a serious financial crime.",
